# Layout width (enforced + drift-resistant)

## Default (removes ambiguity)

**If unsure → use `<Container>` or `<Section>` with `maxWidth`.**  
Do not add raw `max-w-*` until you know the column is not a standard screen token.

`npm run check` runs `scripts/check-layout-width.js`, which imports **`scripts/layout-width-policy.js`** — the **only** place allowed utilities and arbitrary literals are enumerated.

---

## Two systems (do not duplicate on one node)

| System | Where | Mechanism |
|--------|--------|-----------|
| **Tokens** | Reusable layout, marketing bands | `Container` / `Section` → `max-w-screen-*` / `full` |
| **Fixed scale** | Routes, demos, stories, showcase | Approved `max-w-*` from policy, or `Page className` |

---

## Arbitrary `max-w-[…]` (frozen set)

Each entry in **`ARBITRARY_MAX_WIDTH`** in `scripts/layout-width-policy.js` has:

- **`id`** — stable name for review/PRs  
- **`category`** — `app-shell` | `demo` | `intrinsic` | …  
- **`purpose`** — one-line why it exists  

Current literals:

| Literal | ID | Category |
|---------|-----|----------|
| `max-w-[266px]` | DOCS_CATALOG_SIDEBAR_CAP | app-shell |
| `max-w-[280px]` | SIDEBAR_APP_SHELL_RAIL | demo |
| `max-w-[min(24rem,calc(100vw-2rem))]` | TOAST_INLINE_VIEWPORT | intrinsic (Toast only) |

Optional **named aliases** (must stay in sync): `src/lib/layout-width-tokens.ts`.

**No new arbitrary values** without updating the policy object **and** a PR that states use case + category.

---

## Packaged components

Only these files may contain **any** `max-w-*`:

- `atoms/Container.svelte`, `atoms/Toast.svelte`, `molecules/Section.svelte`, `organisms/TopNavbar.svelte`

**Organism rule:** only **TopNavbar** may embed inner chrome width (`max-w-7xl` row). Other organisms: width from parent.

---

## Before expanding the allowlist (review checklist)

1. **Use case** — docs | demo | marketing | app-shell | chrome | intrinsic  
2. **Rejected alternative** — why not `Container`/`Section` or an existing fixed utility?  
3. **Policy update** — edit **`layout-width-policy.js`** (`ALLOWED_GLOBAL_MAX_W` and/or `ARBITRARY_MAX_WIDTH`)  
4. **Docs** — adjust this rule file if the mental model changes  
5. **`npm run check`** must pass  

Banned shortcuts: pasting new `max-w-*` in components to “fix” layout, or adding arbitrary literals without `ARBITRARY_MAX_WIDTH` metadata.

---

## Failure output

Violations print **category**, **why**, and **exact replacement** (see `BANNED_UTILITY_REPLACEMENTS` in policy). Footer: default rule + policy path.

